Privacy Policy for Nearby
Effective Date: [09-07-2025]
1. Introduction
Nearby is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application Nearby.
2. Information We Collect
a. Personal Information
Account Information: When you sign up, we collect your email address and other profile information you provide (such as username, full name, and profile photo).
Authentication: We use Supabase for authentication and user management.
b. Location Data
Precise Location: With your permission, we collect your device’s location to provide location-based features (such as showing nearby events and challenges).
Usage: Location data is only used while the app is in use and is not shared with third parties except as necessary to provide app functionality.
c. Device Permissions
The app may request access to:
Location: To show nearby events and challenges.
Camera and Photos: To allow you to upload a profile photo or event images.
Notifications: To send you updates about events, challenges, and other app activity.
d. Usage Data
We may collect information about how you use the app, such as feature usage, crash logs, and device information, to improve the app.
3. How We Use Your Information
We use your information to:
Provide and maintain the app’s core features.
Personalize your experience.
Communicate with you about updates, events, and challenges.
Improve app performance and security.
Comply with legal obligations.
4. How We Share Your Information
We do not sell your personal information. We may share your information:
With service providers (such as Supabase and Google/Firebase) to enable app functionality.
If required by law or to protect rights, property, or safety.
5. Data Security
We use industry-standard security measures to protect your data. However, no method of transmission or storage is 100% secure.
6. Your Choices
Permissions: You can control app permissions (location, camera, notifications) in your device settings.
Account: You may update or delete your account at any time from within the app.
7. Children’s Privacy
Our app is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect data from children under 13.
8. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by updating the effective date and, if significant, by in-app notification.
9. Contact Us
If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, contact us at:
Gmail : adityavkharat@gmail.com
